Embark on a journey to wellness with these
5 Medicinal Teas!🌱

1️⃣Cinnamon Tea: Boil a gup of water with 1 inch piece of cinnamon stick for 5 minutes, 
Strain and enjoy this soothing, blood sugar regulating tea.

2️⃣Cumin Coriander Fennel Tea: Mix equal parts of each of cumin, coriander and fennel seeds. Boil a teaspoon of this mixture in a cup of water for 5-7 minutes.
Strain and sip to ease stomach discomfort and reduce bloating.

3️⃣Hibiscus Tea: Steep 1 tsp of dried hibiscus flowers in boiling water for 5 minutes. Strain and enjoy this antioxidant-rich, heart-healthy tea either hot or cold.

4️⃣Mint Tea: Steep fresh or dried mint eaves in boiling water for 5-7 minutes. Strain and enjoy this refreshing tea that’s great for digestion and stress relief.

5️⃣Chamomile Tea: Steep a chamomile tea bag or dried chamomile flowers in hot water for 5 minutes.
Strain and enjoy this calming tea that’s perfect for a good night’s sleep 

Embrace the natural healing powers of these teas and make them a part of /our daily routine for a healthier, happier you!😇❤️

Gut Health🤢

Gut health means your stomach and intestines are working well, and the good bacteria in your belly are happy. When your gut is healthy:
- You digest food properly
- You poop at a fix time everyday
- You feel less bloated or gassy
- Your mood and energy are better
- Your immunity stays strong

👉🏻Do these 7 things for a Healthy GUT : 

1. Have Chach/ Buttermilk with your Lunch - Best Summer Probiotic 😍
2. Stop taking Stress - it leads to Stress Eating😳
3. Add Ghee to your food, and more healthy fats - nuts, seeds, olive oil, dark chocolate🍫
4. Stop having Fruits after Meals , No Fruits at Night time🍎
5. Stop having Sugar & other processed food to fulfill your cravings🧁 
6. Stop drinking Water while eating your food. Drink water after 30 minutes of your meal 🚰
7. Don’t lie down after Eating Sit in Vajrasana for 2-5 minutes Walk for 5-10 minutes🚶🏻‍♂️ 

Try this out & let me know your results in comments 😇

Non-alcoholic fatty liver disease (NAFLD) is the term for a range of conditions caused by a build-up of fat in the liver. It’s usually seen in people who are overweight or obese.😨

Early-stage Non alcoholic fatty liver does not usually cause any harm, but it can lead to serious liver damage, including cirrhosis, if it gets worse.‼️‼️

Having high levels of fat in your liver is also associated with an increased risk of serious health problems, such as diabetes, high blood pressure and kidney disease ‼️
